rComments: Keiko is a great teacher. There is quite a lot of reading for this course but it is really interesting. She is extremely patient and kind.

Keiko what to say about her...I believe she knows her stuff but she is just not able to teach it. She struggle a lot to explain very basic concept and spend more than 30 minutes explaining the same thing with inadequate examples. The final exam was so hard and not representing of what she is teaching. Avoid at all costs......

it is very hard to understand what she really mean. Honestly, TA's were more helpful than her. Not to consider as a an easy course. it is more confusing than ever, but when the TA's explain it is way more simple and easy.

Hard to understand. Make simple concept very complited more than they should be. If you have previous years assignments and exams you will get through this class, but if not, d'ont even cosider taking this class! All you will learn is OKAY. Not recommanded...
I felt everytime I left the class I some how knew less then when I went in. I truly believe she really knows her stuff but she is really unable to teach it to you.
She says 'okay?' a lot to confirm if you understand. You won't, of course. You'll learn more if you don't go to lectures.

She is very hard to understand until you learn to speak "keiko"... but she really does know her stuff and is very willing to help.  Her teaching methods are not great, she tends to focus too much on straight memorization and not enough on concepts overall. Favourite quote: "Crystal clear??"
